<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="un1013b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013b"> (NLI.3) 13(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> to sense the universal love:</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Study in Christian Gnosticism&rdquo; 334: In Buddhist terms, the Master taught one and the same Truth; but it appeared different according to the capacities of the hearers;&mdash;according as they could perceive only the energy of the Nirm&amacr;&#x1E47;a-k&amacr;ya or the Activity of Transformation, giving rise to the formal teaching, or earthly aspect, or sensible mode; or according as they could <mark>sense the universal love</mark> (love for all that lives and breathes) of the Sa&#7745;bhoga-k&amacr;ya, or the Activity of Bliss; or according as they could realise the supreme actuality of immediate identification with the Dharma-k&amacr;ya&mdash;the Buddha in absolute Truth. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G.R.S. Mead, &ldquo;The Secret of Jesus</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07255g" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07255g">VI.C.07:255(g)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
